

'''=  active hackerspace in Tirana, Albania: "providing tools that bring knowledge closer to those more in need".'''

URL = http://openlabs.cc/


=Description=

'''1.'''

"We are a non-government non-profit organization, based in Albania, that aims to support and promote initiatives which provide tools that bring knowledge closer to those more in need.

Our energy and resources are dedicated to make knowledge a weapon that opens new horizons to children of all ages, organizations, local communities and everyday people like you.

We organize weekly events in Tirana and other cities so don't forget to come back here from time to time."
(http://openlabs.cc/)


'''2. Open-Steps:'''

"Open Labs is the one of its kind in this country. Its members ( about 20 ) are working hard to change this by promoting knowledge sharing and open cultures, and establishing a network with similar organisations from neighbour countries. Active members count also youngsters under 20 and their motivation has made the first year very successful.

Since its creation, Open Labs has been hosting weekly events, meetings and regular workshops ( about wordpress, linux, audacity…). Other projects managed by its members include the educational electronics kit called WMKIT which has been also presented at Betahaus in Berlin or the development of the wikipedia in the albanian language."
(http://www.open-steps.org/workshop-open-labs-tirana-albania/)

